Spanish Data Protection Law (LOPDGDD): The LOPDGDD is the primary law governing data protection in Spain. It applies to all organizations that process personal data of individuals located in Spain, regardless of where the organization is located. The LOPDGDD is based on the GDPR, but it also includes some additional requirements.
Spanish ePrivacy Law (LSSI): The LSSI is a law that regulates the use of cookies and other tracking technologies.It applies to all websites that target individuals located in Spain. The LSSI requires websites to obtain consent from individuals before using cookies or other tracking technologies.

General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR): The GDPR is the primary law governing data protection in the European Union. It applies to all organizations that process personal data of individuals located in the EU, regardless of where the organization is located. The GDPR requires organizations to obtain consent from individuals
before collecting or processing their personal data, and to take appropriate security measures to protect their personal data.
ePrivacy Directive: The ePrivacy Directive is a law that regulates the use of cookies and other tracking technologies. It applies to all websites that target individuals located in the European Union. The ePrivacy Directive requires websites to obtain consent from individuals before using cookies or other tracking technologies.
Country-specific laws: In addition to the GDPR and the ePrivacy Directive, there may be additional laws and regulations that apply to the collection and processing of personal emails in your specific country. For example, in Germany, the Federal Data Protection Act (BDSG) imposes additional requirements on the processing of personal data.
  
